""""Properly"""" ..lol there isnt anything you can do wrong besides not plug in the iron.. Use a dense nickel sized nug place it in a peice of folded wax or parchment paper set straightening iron between 260-300 once hot place folded paper in iron. Place iron on a book and use another book to press and just press hard af for 3-5 seconds ( more pressure more rosin ) if you hear a sizzle stop. Be careful scraping the rosin off the paper if you tear it it ends up being a big pain in the ass to recover the rest of the rosin. Save your spent herb to make butter.
